webpackJsonp([0xf07690a61457],{758:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"weiran.co",author:"Weiran Zhang"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/weiran/git/weiran/weiran.co/src/pages/blog/2012/7/the-verge-office-2013-preview/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>I like the <a href="http://www.theverge.com/2012/7/16/3156636/office-2013-screenshots-features-preview">new look of Office 2013</a> and the “cloud” integration, but as The Verge reports:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The touch experience isn’t great from my own testing on Windows 8 Release Preview, and it feels all too familiar to Windows 7 — a first stab at touch improvements on desktop software. Microsoft’s Office division has taken a similar approach, by increasing touch targets, but it seems that any truly touch-optimized versions of Office will come as Metro style apps, if anything at all. It’s clearly difficult to create a fully functional touch-based word processor or spreadsheet with legacy support, and Microsoft hasn’t cracked it yet.</p>\n</blockquote>',frontmatter:{title:"The Verge: Office 2013 Preview",date:"July 16, 2012",passthroughUrl:null}}},pathContext:{slug:"/blog/2012/7/the-verge-office-2013-preview/",previous:{fields:{slug:"/blog/2012/7/google-galaxy-7-unboxing/"},frontmatter:{title:"Google Galaxy 7 Unboxing",passthroughUrl:null}},next:{fields:{slug:"/blog/2012/7/unsolicited-advice-for-marissa-mayer/"},frontmatter:{title:"Unsolicited Advice for Marissa Mayer",passthroughUrl:null}}}}}});
